Description:

Ingrao, Inc is seeking a talented Architectural Renderer to join our tight-knit team!
With projects all over the world, Ingrao Inc. has not only redefined the world of modern luxury, but has become a name synonymous with refinement, quality and unique style. Light, texture, scale, unexpected unique materials and the relationship between the interior and its surroundings are at the forefront of Ingrao's design process. Ingrao Inc. are widely known for private residential projects in New York, Los Angeles, Santa Barbara, Aspen, Hawaii, The Caribbean and Miami, and have also completed projects in Tel Aviv, Monaco, St. Tropez, Moscow, Paris and Hong Kong.
The Role
We are looking for a full-time office-based Visualization Specialist to join the design team at our Manhattan office. The candidate will work alongside architects and interior designers to portray the spaces we design to our clients, driving the narrative and evoking a compelling sense of place; of lighting, texture and mood through the creation of photorealistic imagery and vignettes.
Desired skills:
A thorough and in-depth knowledge of Photoshop, Rhino, 3DS Max and V-Ray is essential, as well as experience with AutoCAD and the ability to read and interpret architectural plans and technical drawings;
Thorough knowledge of the technical process of creating a photorealistic image, including lighting, camera set-up, texturing etc;
The foresight to choose the most appropriate workflow for the situation;
Aptitude to work under tight deadlines and excellent time management skills;
Ability to receive artistic and technical critique and act upon it as and where appropriate;
Ability to interpret ambiguous aesthetic direction;
Strong communication skills and ability to provide a clear indication of project timeframes and manage expectations of team members;
Strong passion for the visual arts, for 3d rendering and CGI technologies and the possibilities and potential that they bring;
Highly refined presentation skills;
Legal authorization to work in the US and fluency in English.
We are looking for a candidate with a keen eye for design and composition; somebody who can manipulate light and shadow, color and texture, and tell a story through imagery.
Application
Please note that this is not a freelance or remote-work position. This is a full-time, studio-based role in New York, USA, for an immediate start.


Ferguson &Shamamian Architects is seeking an Architect or Designer interested in architecture visualization for a full time position as a digital renderer.  Responsibilities include generating finished digital renderings suitable for client presentation and display in a variety of settings with the ability to work under pressure, shifting priorities and multiple deadlines. Must possess 3-5 years of relevant working experience in 3D illustrations and renderings and interested in career growth in a small team environment. 

Role Requirements:
	Degree or Diploma in Architecture or Design;
	Strong organizational ability;
	Strong ability to focus on details;
	Understanding of project design approach and workflow;
	Capability to read and understand architectural drawings;
	Advanced skill set in AutoCAD, Sketchup and 3D Studio Max;
	Advanced skill set in using V-ray for interior and exterior renderings; 
	Highly skilled in Adobe Photoshop, specifically in rendering lighting, texture, form, and performing post production work and creating compositions.

The hours are 9:00 a.m. to 6:00 p.m. with minimal overtime. Positive attitude, teamwork and professional appearance are essential. We offer competitive benefits including medical, dental, vision and disability insurance, 401(k) plan, profit sharing plan and bonuses. Visit our website www.fergusonshamamian.com.

Please send cover letter, resume and work samples to Employment@fergusonshamamian.com and input Digital Renderer 091018-002 in the subject line. No phone calls please.


